1. 

In this Order— 

“the Act of 1976” means the Family Law (Maintenance of Spouses and 
Children) Act 1976 (No. 11 of 1976); 

the “Act of 1987” means the Status of Children Act 1987 (No. 26 of 1987); 

the “Act of 1995” means the Family Law Act 1995 (No. 26 of 1995); 

the “Act of 1996” means the Family Law (Divorce) Act 1996 (No. 33 of 1996); 

the “Act of 2010” means the Civil Partnership and Certain Rights and 
Obligations of Cohabitants Act 2010 (No. 24 of 2010); 

the “Act of 2015” means the Children and Family Relationships Act 2015 (No. 
9 of 2015); 

“competent authority” has the meaning assigned to it in Order 98. 

Venue.
